King K, the gentleboy. ♥️
You guys, I am so proud of Kukhanya. This year has been challenging for him but he’s come out on top. 

Starting school after 4 years of being at home meant getting used to a new schedule, new environment and new people. Nothing prepared me for the physical toll it took on his little body- the amount of times he got sick this year had us SHOOK. It felt like every other week was something new and he was absolutely terrified each time. There were lots of sleepless nights, tears and difficult questions but he got through it and we did too. I am so grateful. 

I’m also so amazed at his social skills. He used to take a long time acclimating to new people and would often withdraw into himself in social settings but now he’s openly engaging; confidently so. He’s really coming to himself and I can’t wait to see him develop further.

At what stage did you little ones start daycare/school and how did they handle it?

☀️share your experience to help out another mommy.

My internal self despises the amount of pressure women are under to be beautiful, to have perfect skin, perfect hair, to be skinny or ‘fat’ in a socially acceptable way; y’know with curves and an angular face, I absolutely hate it.

I also feel like a hypocrite because I will do things to make myself feel more beautiful even though I believe that beautiful is the least valuable thing I can be. I have so much more to offer the world than a beautiful face and nice figure but often feel like I’m often reduced to that in any case and fighting it is so much work. And I’m tired. I don’t want to live my life always in protest. I don’t want to always be justifying my actions yet sometimes feel the need to? 

Anyway, it’s 5pm and my English bundles are running out and I’ve got assignments to do so I’m gonna leave this rant here for myself to come back to one day and continue figuring out exactly what I think and where I was going with this. Lol.
Sorry for wasting your time xoxo

So…. I didn’t wear shorts ALL summer, besides in the house, then on this cloudy and rainy day, I really wanted to wear the two piece that had been rotting in my closet for months so I just did it. Regardless of the weather, regardless of my currently complicated relationship with my body- I did it. And I was so glad.

This anecdote is just to say that it’s normal to have a love-hate-love relationship with your body. We all have insecurities. Some days I look in the mirror and feel like the most beautiful person in the world and some days I feel like a freaking potato. But that doesn’t change the fact that this body is home. 

I know a lot of the time when women have kids and our bodies change we always feel grateful that it carried our kids and credit that as one of the reasons it deserves to be love in its imperfections but I’ve realised that even if I didn’t have kids- my body might have still changed but it would still be carrying me, my memories, a part of my sense of self and it would still be worthy of love and appreciation. 

So weather you have kids or you don’t, give your body room to evolve and live as freely as you can with it. Express yourself through it without fear and regardless of insecurities.

Don’t let those insecurities stop you from wearing what you want to wear. No one cares, we’re all dealing with a cost of living crisis anyway. 😂

I woke up feeling the need to stop and take a moment to be grateful for my life today. 

There was a day when we were all sitting in the kids’ room while Sabelo told them a bedtime story and I was so happy I almost cried. I’m so grateful that I get to experience the person I love being a present, consistent, loving, playful, engaging and gentle father. Watching my kids playing, snuggling and connecting with their dad is one of my favourite things. It’s almost addictive, lol, like the more I experience it, the more I want to feel the emotions I experience in those moments over and over again. 

On most days we get so busy that there are rarely moments to sit back and take it all in but I’m so grateful for my people. I love my family so much. I love my partner for always trying his best. My boys have such an amazing father man. 🥺

Lol I’m definitely crying while writing this. My heart is swollen with gratitude and so so much love. I’m exactly where I need to be and I pray I always remember that on hard days. ❤️

What are you grateful for today?

Today reminded me of what is most important to me in my parenting journey. Seeing my children happy and actively enjoying their lives. Simple moments that are bursting with joy. Every day magic. 

I think I forget how uncomplicated happiness is. Of course, it’s a matter of perspective but I’ve always believed, at my core, that it’s not something I should have to wait for, or only feel when x or y happens. There are so many pockets of joy that are constant and often overlooked. 

Children remind me of the ease of laughter. The warmth of being surrounded by love. The accessibility of joy. It’s there and I hate that I forget to look sometimes. 

Anyway, this was a great night. I heard them giggling when they were meant to be sleeping and instead of ruining what was a pure moment of joy I decided to join in. Rules were suspended and lots of hugs, laughs and expressions of love were shared.

Monday morning might be a little bit of a drag but it certainly will be worth it. ❤️

Did you know that there is currently an outbreak of measles in SA? Has your child received their measles vaccine? 

As parents, I think we can all agree that our children's health is one of our top priorities. Having a sick child is stressful and costly; emotionally, financially and physically. Last year, our Kukhanya contracted measles at school and it was such a difficult experience. We found ourselves in the emergency room in the middle of the night after he had a fever. It was  overwhelming for everyone but mostly for him. I remember him asking us when he going to stop feeling the discomfort he was feeling and it broke my heart. We got through it but it was honestly a very challenging time.

Luckily his symptoms weren't as terrible as they could have been because he'd had his measles vaccinations as a toddler but with the current measles outbreak, I wish we'd had time and notice to get the additional vaccination. 

It's so important to do what we can to protect our children from potential infections especially at a time when there is an outbreak. Not every child is vaccinated and that results in more infections. If you haven't already, I urge you to take your child to get vaccinated so that you can have peace of mind and protect your child. Follow the @departmentofhealth_za pages for more info.

#oneshotformeasles #itsnothingnew #stopmeaslesvaccinate

How was your start to this fifth and, thankfully, final week of this month?

This week I’m practicing gratitude, hard. It’s been a trying season and I feel like I’ve been all over the place- even as a mom- I have not been my best but I’m surviving and trying my best at all times even though my best looks different depending on the day. I’m working myself to a better place and the return of warmth is really helping me along. 

I’m sharing this to reminder myself (and anyone else who needs to hear it) that the best you can always do is to try. Sometimes showing up is easy and you know you’re doing a great job. Sometimes you show up and try and feel like your efforts are inadequate. It’s normal. We try again in the next minute, the next hour, the next day… we try again, always. 🤍

Last night the family and I joined Norman and his friends on a crazy adventure and it was such a thrill!

Now… I don’t want to ruin @headspacemovie for you, if you haven’t seen it yet, but let’s just say if you’ve ever heard voices in your head you might want to investigate.😂 On the serious note, Headspace is a locally produced, all South African, animated film with a nail-biting plot, amazing visuals and captivating voiceover work. 
The film encourages teamwork, confidence and creativity; which are great qualities to inspire in children and as a mom- I loved seeing that. 

If you need a family activity for the weekend, this is it! A family movie date is always a great idea; especially when the kids get to watch other children save the planet.🥺

‘You need not say, “I love you.” to your lover,
Rather, aim for your lover to say, “You truly love me.”
For the presence, absence, and intensity of Love is affirmed by those that it is directed to.
When the sun rises, does it declare to the earth that, “I have risen!”?
Is it not the birds that welcome its presence with a song?
The flowers that open up to experience its expression?
The fields that feed off its radiance?
(…)

When you love,
Love such that her eyes sing to the very sight of you,
Such that his ears open to experience your every expression,
Such that your beings feed off your energy and radiance,
Such that your entire existence wakes to your light and exclaims the intensity 
of your Love.’

-@vusumuzi_phakathi

I am currently dwelling in moments, taking stock of all my blessings and practicing gratitude. 2023 was TRYING so this holiday season, for me, is essentially for rest, time away from SM & the world, self-care and intentional prolonged moments of connection with my loved ones. 

I hope you have had a lovely festive season this far. 
I hope the Christmas holidays, whether you celebrate Christmas itself or not, have afforded you an opportunity to rest your body and your mind. I hope your spirit has been reinvigorated and that your heart has been revelling in love. 

Now more than ever, I hope kindness is the order of the day, so many people need it. 
Happy Holidays, my lovelies.
xoxo 🫶🏾
B R E A T H E 🤍

This year brought out all the vernac in me; I don’t have the English for it-even though English is the language I usually best express myself in; all I have is ‘YHO HAYI, NKOSI.’😭 Multilingual people know that when you cry, you cry in your mother tongue and not in a borrowed language. 😂

Anyhow, I hope 2024 shows you that there is always reason to believe. I hope whenever you fall, you always have a soft landing. I hope you find the lessons in all the failures you’ve had thus far and those you may have; and that they make you a better you. 
I hope your willingness to try against all odds never subsides. I hope the universe shows you WHY it’s always worth fighting and getting back up. I hope what is important to you, remains untouched and whole. 

I wish for you every day, small acts of kindness in 2024. I wish you warmth and butterfly kisses. I wish you sweet and unwavering love. I wish you contentment within yourself. I wish for you and your loved ones uncharted joy and prosperity. 

May your cup overflow and fridge always be full. 
LOVE YOU 🫵🏾🫶🏾

P.S Thank you for another year of community, support, kind messages + comments and all the love!

If you’re reading this, you made it to the other side. 🫶🏾
Here’s a slice of cake from me to you 😋 

#happy2024 my lovelies!
